1
00:00:00,390 --> 00:00:02,840
Previously on Fairy Tail:

2
00:00:02,840 --> 00:00:05,150
Edolas, the homeland of Carla and myself!

3
00:00:05,150 --> 00:00:08,050
I'm glad we made it there to 
search for our missing friends,

4
00:00:08,050 --> 00:00:11,250
but there's a whole lot of things 
different in this world...

5
00:00:11,250 --> 00:00:13,910
We can't use magic? I never 
heard of something like that!

6
00:00:14,150 --> 00:00:16,640
Everyone at the guild is acting odd...

7
00:00:16,640 --> 00:00:18,970
What in the world is going on?!

8
00:01:53,890 --> 00:01:55,960
Who the hell are you?

9
00:01:56,750 --> 00:01:59,530
What the hell are you doing 
sneaking around under there?

10
00:02:01,760 --> 00:02:04,030
What's wrong with everyone?

11
00:02:05,080 --> 00:02:07,060
Lucy-san is scary...

12
00:02:08,990 --> 00:02:09,960
Natsu?

13
00:02:15,690 --> 00:02:18,730
Now I take a closer look at ya, you're Natsu!

14
00:02:19,450 --> 00:02:20,920
Natsu, she says?

15
00:02:20,920 --> 00:02:22,650
What's with the outfit?

16
00:02:23,790 --> 00:02:26,210
Natsu... Where have you...

17
00:02:26,500 --> 00:02:28,040
Where have you been this whole time?

18
00:02:29,090 --> 00:02:31,060
You had me worried, damn it!

19
00:02:34,120 --> 00:02:35,490
Fairy Hunting.

20
00:02:39,140 --> 00:02:40,820
Lucy?

21
00:02:41,930 --> 00:02:43,800
Capital Punishment!

22
00:02:43,800 --> 00:02:45,110
There it is!

23
00:02:45,110 --> 00:02:47,560
One of Lucy's 48 torture techniques:

24
00:02:47,560 --> 00:02:49,230
The Screwdrive Crush!

25
00:02:50,250 --> 00:02:51,940
Natsu-san!

26
00:02:52,460 --> 00:02:55,580
It's not nice to pick on him like that...

27
00:02:56,270 --> 00:02:58,890
I can't believe that's actually Cana!

28
00:02:59,740 --> 00:03:03,380
And over here, too! I can't 
believe that's actually Elfman!

29
00:03:03,380 --> 00:03:05,820
How long are ya gonna keep sobbing, you wimp!

30
00:03:05,820 --> 00:03:07,800
I'm so sorry!

31
00:03:08,120 --> 00:03:10,070
I don't get this at all!

32
00:03:10,070 --> 00:03:12,710
What in the world is going on?

33
00:03:12,710 --> 00:03:14,630
Well, at least I'm glad you're safe.

34
00:03:15,090 --> 00:03:17,100
Right, Juvia-chan?

35
00:03:17,100 --> 00:03:18,260
Shut up.

36
00:03:18,260 --> 00:03:21,570
Is this all the effect of Edolas?

37
00:03:21,570 --> 00:03:24,320
Is everything and everyone 
completely backwards?

38
00:03:25,670 --> 00:03:28,530
Natsu, welcome back!

39
00:03:29,180 --> 00:03:30,590
Mira's the same as always.

40
00:03:30,590 --> 00:03:32,360
Well, that's unexpectedly boring.

41
00:03:34,310 --> 00:03:35,870
By the way...

42
00:03:36,230 --> 00:03:39,300
Who are the girl and those cats?

43
00:03:39,300 --> 00:03:40,350
Cats?

44
00:03:41,180 --> 00:03:42,580
Cats?!

45
00:03:42,580 --> 00:03:44,500
There are cats here!

46
00:03:44,500 --> 00:03:45,970
Cats?!

47
00:03:45,970 --> 00:03:47,160
What's the meaning of this?

48
00:03:47,160 --> 00:03:49,420
Why are Exceeds here in a place like this?

49
00:03:51,150 --> 00:03:52,210
Exceeds?

50
00:03:56,380 --> 00:03:58,670
W-What?

51
00:03:58,670 --> 00:04:00,890
What's going on here?

52
00:04:01,240 --> 00:04:05,510
Why is everyone so scared when 
they hear the word "Exceed"?

53
00:04:05,510 --> 00:04:07,110
What's an "Exceed"?

54
00:04:07,110 --> 00:04:08,090
Carla...

55
00:04:11,190 --> 00:04:13,540
Phew, it was getting really hot.

56
00:04:13,540 --> 00:04:15,120
You really look just like them.

57
00:04:16,190 --> 00:04:18,900
You two look like Exceeds!

58
00:04:18,900 --> 00:04:21,770
Uh, do they look <i>like</i> them?

59
00:04:21,770 --> 00:04:23,540
Or are they actually real ones?

60
00:04:23,540 --> 00:04:25,200
It's just like Nee-chan said...

61
00:04:25,870 --> 00:04:28,250
They just <i>look</i> exactly like Exceeds, is all.

62
00:04:28,250 --> 00:04:29,720
Well, guess that's that.

63
00:04:29,720 --> 00:04:31,410
I suppose...

64
00:04:31,410 --> 00:04:33,620
They really do look just like cats, though...

65
00:04:33,890 --> 00:04:35,720
Uh...

66
00:04:35,720 --> 00:04:37,330
Hey, don't take it off!

67
00:04:37,780 --> 00:04:40,300
But it's all stuffy!

68
00:04:40,300 --> 00:04:42,340
Deal with it!

69
00:04:51,950 --> 00:04:54,060
Lucy-san is scary.

70
00:04:54,060 --> 00:04:57,330
Now, spit it out! I was really 
damn worried about you!

71
00:04:57,330 --> 00:04:59,130
Where were you and what 
the hell were you doing?

72
00:04:59,130 --> 00:05:01,180
Uh, how should I start...

73
00:05:01,180 --> 00:05:04,790
Natsu, you have to explain 
everything carefully!

74
00:05:05,230 --> 00:05:08,320
You know, that... It's like, uh...

75
00:05:09,700 --> 00:05:12,630
You are <i>so</i> annoying!

76
00:05:13,580 --> 00:05:14,950
There it is!

77
00:05:14,950 --> 00:05:17,410
This time it's the Screwdrive Elbow Crush!

78
00:05:17,410 --> 00:05:19,380
The only difference is the elbow?

79
00:05:19,680 --> 00:05:21,060
Bis Bis...

80
00:05:21,060 --> 00:05:22,880
What is it, Al Al?

81
00:05:22,880 --> 00:05:26,050
Maybe we should get going on 
a job, just the two of us!

82
00:05:26,050 --> 00:05:29,100
Let's go, let's go! What kind 
of job would you like, Al Al?

83
00:05:29,100 --> 00:05:30,410
Hmm, let me see...

84
00:05:30,410 --> 00:05:33,090
Let's go on a job that you enjoy, Bis Bis!

85
00:05:33,410 --> 00:05:36,450
Al Al, you're so kind!

86
00:05:37,590 --> 00:05:40,220
They really, really get along...

87
00:05:40,220 --> 00:05:44,470
Even with everything backwards, I 
think there should be limits...

88
00:05:44,470 --> 00:05:47,910
So, Juvia-chan... You said 
you were going on a job?

89
00:05:47,910 --> 00:05:50,170
I sure wish I could go with you...

90
00:05:50,170 --> 00:05:52,530
And I told you to stay away from me.

91
00:05:52,530 --> 00:05:53,890
You're so smothering...

92
00:05:53,890 --> 00:05:56,390
Juvia is going on a job by herself.

93
00:05:56,390 --> 00:05:59,100
Because you're no help at all.

94
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:04,570
Gray-san, don't you think you should give up?

95
00:06:04,570 --> 00:06:08,240
It was true for Leon-kun, too... 
But I'm not seeing any hope here.

96
00:06:08,240 --> 00:06:11,600
Don't say the name of that 
bundled-up playboy in front of me!

97
00:06:11,600 --> 00:06:14,510
Juvia-chan, I'm begging you!

98
00:06:14,560 --> 00:06:15,990
You're a pest!

99
00:06:17,250 --> 00:06:18,800
Help me!

100
00:06:19,670 --> 00:06:22,740
And help <i>me</i>!

101
00:06:24,930 --> 00:06:26,650
Reedus?

102
00:06:26,650 --> 00:06:29,570
Sheesh... Stop lounging around!

103
00:06:29,570 --> 00:06:30,770
You'll get yourself hurt!

104
00:06:30,770 --> 00:06:32,360
You damn fake Exceed!

105
00:06:32,630 --> 00:06:34,050
Fake?!

106
00:06:34,050 --> 00:06:37,120
I don't really understand, 
but I'm not a fake!

107
00:06:38,780 --> 00:06:42,030
Gray, don't be a lazy bum! Get up!

108
00:06:42,030 --> 00:06:46,170
It's warm and comfy down here...

109
00:06:46,170 --> 00:06:47,960
You're a lazy bum, and an embarrassment!

110
00:06:47,960 --> 00:06:51,470
Technique 35: The Bitch Drop!

111
00:06:51,970 --> 00:06:55,010
Technique 28: The Give-Up-Already Lock!

112
00:06:56,180 --> 00:06:58,060
Lucy-san is scary.

113
00:06:58,880 --> 00:07:00,330
You ain't getting away, Natsu!

114
00:07:00,330 --> 00:07:01,770
Work, work!

115
00:07:00,330 --> 00:07:02,240
Where are you hiding?

116
00:07:03,280 --> 00:07:06,320
No use... The transmission lines are shot...

117
00:07:06,320 --> 00:07:08,270
On to the next job!

118
00:07:09,210 --> 00:07:11,030
Keep it down, Nab. You suck!

119
00:07:11,030 --> 00:07:12,800
What'd you say?!

120
00:07:12,800 --> 00:07:15,240
What the hell you mean I suck, Levy?

121
00:07:15,240 --> 00:07:18,940
Can't you tell I'm doing some 
delicate maintenance right now?

122
00:07:18,940 --> 00:07:21,750
With you running around all over 
the place, I can't concentrate!

123
00:07:21,750 --> 00:07:23,680
Come on out, Natsu!

124
00:07:23,680 --> 00:07:25,630
I'll try out my new technique on ya!

125
00:07:25,630 --> 00:07:28,030
Keep it down, Lucy! You suck!

126
00:07:28,030 --> 00:07:29,850
What the hell did you say?

127
00:07:29,850 --> 00:07:32,350
I said I was in the middle of maintenance!

128
00:07:32,350 --> 00:07:33,960
You damn amazon woman!

129
00:07:33,960 --> 00:07:35,760
Then hurry the hell up with it!

130
00:07:35,760 --> 00:07:37,750
You skinny mechanic!

131
00:07:37,750 --> 00:07:40,200
Now, now... Calm down, you two.

132
00:07:40,200 --> 00:07:42,730
We're really counting on you, Levy-san.

133
00:07:42,730 --> 00:07:46,070
Without your engineering, 
this guild would be...

134
00:07:47,970 --> 00:07:50,070
We're counting on you to make it quick.

135
00:07:50,400 --> 00:07:52,280
As long as you understand.

136
00:07:53,670 --> 00:07:57,530
Oh, yeah... It doesn't look 
like Erza-san is here...

137
00:07:57,840 --> 00:07:59,500
You gotta be kiddin' me...

138
00:07:59,500 --> 00:08:03,810
Hey, so what do you think 
Erza's like over here?

139
00:08:03,810 --> 00:08:07,220
Well, you know, probably backwards.

140
00:08:07,220 --> 00:08:08,430
Natsu-san...

141
00:08:08,720 --> 00:08:11,380
What's the opposite of Erza, anyway?

142
00:08:11,760 --> 00:08:12,920
Hmm, good question...

143
00:08:13,740 --> 00:08:15,920
You fool!

144
00:08:15,920 --> 00:08:18,440
How many times do I have to tell you?

145
00:08:18,440 --> 00:08:20,460
I'm sorry! I'm sorry!

146
00:08:20,460 --> 00:08:23,350
I'll never hold you back 
again, I promise, Natsu-san!

147
00:08:25,120 --> 00:08:27,330
Fine, as long as you understand!

148
00:08:27,330 --> 00:08:29,590
I'm so honored to have your leadership!

149
00:08:29,590 --> 00:08:30,680
Like that?

150
00:08:30,680 --> 00:08:33,110
Isn't that just your secret desire, Natsu?

151
00:08:33,360 --> 00:08:34,640
Oh yeah?

152
00:08:34,640 --> 00:08:37,060
Then what do you think, Happy?

153
00:08:37,060 --> 00:08:39,850
I think she'd be like this, definitely!

154
00:08:43,310 --> 00:08:46,210
Master Happy, leave this situation to me!

155
00:08:46,210 --> 00:08:47,790
Sure, break a leg!

156
00:08:49,150 --> 00:08:53,300
Master Happy, I will protect 
you, no matter what!

157
00:08:53,540 --> 00:08:55,620
Sure, that's a real load off.

158
00:08:55,620 --> 00:08:57,970
Go forth, my servant Erza...

159
00:08:57,970 --> 00:08:58,790
At your command!

160
00:08:59,350 --> 00:09:00,260
Like that?

161
00:09:00,260 --> 00:09:03,220
No, I think your desire is even worse...

162
00:09:04,510 --> 00:09:06,300
I think she'll be like this!

163
00:09:07,530 --> 00:09:10,450
I improved my cooking skills for you, Wendy!

164
00:09:10,450 --> 00:09:11,980
Now, eat your fill!

165
00:09:13,500 --> 00:09:16,320
Thank you very much! Thanks for the food!

166
00:09:17,110 --> 00:09:19,080
If you eat too much, you'll get cavities...

167
00:09:19,440 --> 00:09:20,280
Like that!

168
00:09:20,280 --> 00:09:21,780
That's where she went?!

169
00:09:22,410 --> 00:09:26,010
Will you people stop fantasizing 
about such trifling trifles?!

170
00:09:27,680 --> 00:09:28,660
But...

171
00:09:28,660 --> 00:09:31,250
An opposite Erza-san...

172
00:09:31,250 --> 00:09:34,110
What would she <i>really</i> be like?

173
00:09:39,420 --> 00:09:40,970
I found you, Natsu!

174
00:09:41,490 --> 00:09:42,630
Hey, you...

175
00:09:42,630 --> 00:09:45,020
Okay! Time to try out my new technique!

176
00:09:45,020 --> 00:09:45,830
I said, stop it!

177
00:09:46,200 --> 00:09:48,730
If you don't cut it out, even if 
you are Lucy, I'm not gonna...

178
00:09:49,860 --> 00:09:51,700
You wanna go?

179
00:09:52,250 --> 00:09:53,930
Be my guest.

180
00:09:58,090 --> 00:10:00,110
S-She's strong!

181
00:10:00,110 --> 00:10:02,640
Natsu, are you okay?

182
00:10:02,640 --> 00:10:04,800
I'm... not okay.

183
00:10:04,800 --> 00:10:06,910
You don't got the guts, chump.

184
00:10:07,180 --> 00:10:10,770
Natsu-san actually talked back to Lucy-san!

185
00:10:10,770 --> 00:10:12,960
That's quite a rare occurrence.

186
00:10:12,960 --> 00:10:14,380
But man, what an idiot.

187
00:10:15,180 --> 00:10:18,600
Now, spit it out! What the hell 
were you doing, and where?

188
00:10:19,410 --> 00:10:21,690
You see... I...

189
00:10:21,690 --> 00:10:23,850
Happy, some help here?

190
00:10:24,720 --> 00:10:28,570
This helmet has been very stuffy 
and I have no strength left.

191
00:10:28,570 --> 00:10:30,040
You cold-hearted...

192
00:10:30,420 --> 00:10:33,520
Lucy... Bullying Natsu again?

193
00:10:33,520 --> 00:10:34,770
Stop it, already.

194
00:10:40,240 --> 00:10:41,700
We're done here.

195
00:10:43,600 --> 00:10:44,660
No way...

196
00:10:45,760 --> 00:10:46,810
You've come back!

197
00:10:47,120 --> 00:10:49,570
Welcome back, Lisanna!

198
00:10:50,310 --> 00:10:53,540
I'm back, Mira-nee, Elf-niichan.

199
00:10:54,720 --> 00:10:57,330
L-Lisanna...

200
00:11:07,750 --> 00:11:08,970
No way...

201
00:11:09,290 --> 00:11:10,260
Lisanna...

202
00:11:11,410 --> 00:11:14,710
Jet, Droy... Don't bully Elf-niichan either!

203
00:11:14,940 --> 00:11:16,780
But...

204
00:11:28,620 --> 00:11:30,150
You'll catch a cold.

205
00:11:31,810 --> 00:11:34,300
Um... Weren't you...

206
00:11:35,140 --> 00:11:36,670
I'm Lisanna!

207
00:11:36,670 --> 00:11:39,250
Oh, I see... You're Mira's little sister?

208
00:11:39,800 --> 00:11:42,880
Don't be out here... Come on inside.

209
00:11:45,090 --> 00:11:47,040
Your name is Natsu, right?

210
00:11:47,040 --> 00:11:50,180
I heard that you were raised by a dragon!

211
00:11:50,180 --> 00:11:51,530
That's amazing!

212
00:11:51,530 --> 00:11:53,090
Huh? Uh, yeah...

213
00:11:53,360 --> 00:11:56,450
I sure wish I could see a dragon...

214
00:11:56,450 --> 00:11:57,730
Yeah, you know?

215
00:11:57,730 --> 00:12:00,470
Igneel is really awesome!

216
00:12:00,470 --> 00:12:02,570
He's so big and strong!

217
00:12:02,570 --> 00:12:05,790
Have you ever heard of Dragon Slayer magic?

218
00:12:05,790 --> 00:12:07,840
Come on, let's go back inside and talk.

219
00:12:07,840 --> 00:12:09,160
Uh, sure!

220
00:12:14,910 --> 00:12:16,930
When we grow up...

221
00:12:17,880 --> 00:12:20,580
...can I be your wife?

222
00:12:20,880 --> 00:12:22,590
How pretty...

223
00:12:23,120 --> 00:12:26,990
I wish this instant would last forever...

224
00:12:30,320 --> 00:12:31,270
Welcome home!

225
00:12:31,990 --> 00:12:33,770
Huh? Oh, right...

226
00:12:34,030 --> 00:12:36,200
Wel-come Ho-me!

227
00:12:37,200 --> 00:12:39,100
I-I'm home?

228
00:12:43,810 --> 00:12:46,200
What are you doing, Lisanna?

229
00:12:47,280 --> 00:12:49,750
It's a grave for Elf-niichan's parakeet...

230
00:12:50,090 --> 00:12:52,560
He made that himself?

231
00:12:52,560 --> 00:12:54,400
He really loved it...

232
00:12:54,690 --> 00:12:56,750
Pretty skilled...

233
00:12:56,750 --> 00:13:00,590
Then, you'll make my grave 
for me, right, Natsu?

234
00:13:01,520 --> 00:13:03,210
Why're you saying something like that?

235
00:13:04,290 --> 00:13:06,810
You're gonna die too, Lisanna?

236
00:13:07,400 --> 00:13:10,630
Hey, stop it! Don't be morbid!

237
00:13:11,010 --> 00:13:13,950
Well, we all die sometime...

238
00:13:20,120 --> 00:13:22,180
She stopped breathing, and then...

239
00:13:22,180 --> 00:13:23,730
There wasn't anything left?

240
00:13:23,730 --> 00:13:26,610
If we could at least bury her...

241
00:13:32,720 --> 00:13:38,410
Hey, Natsu... There's a grave in the 
church, so why are you making one here?

242
00:13:38,930 --> 00:13:40,970
She's not in a place like that.

243
00:13:41,550 --> 00:13:44,290
Besides, she likes the sunset here...

244
00:13:44,910 --> 00:13:48,050
Here, she'll be able to 
watch it all she wants.

245
00:13:48,570 --> 00:13:49,650
Aye...

246
00:13:52,740 --> 00:13:55,770
Even though I promised...

247
00:13:57,230 --> 00:14:00,690
Even though I promised I'd find her...

248
00:14:01,980 --> 00:14:02,710
Aye...

249
00:14:09,740 --> 00:14:10,700
Natsu!

250
00:14:13,690 --> 00:14:15,170
I'm heading out!

251
00:14:18,610 --> 00:14:24,180
Hey... If I disappear again sometime...

252
00:14:24,800 --> 00:14:26,910
Will you come and find me, Natsu?

253
00:14:31,980 --> 00:14:33,050
I've found you...

254
00:14:34,590 --> 00:14:36,270
Lisanna!

255
00:14:36,270 --> 00:14:38,230
Hey!

256
00:14:38,670 --> 00:14:42,100
Since when did you start 
acting like an animal?

257
00:14:43,260 --> 00:14:46,730
But Lisanna is alive... Right over there...

258
00:14:46,730 --> 00:14:48,440
What the hell are you talking about?

259
00:14:50,350 --> 00:14:52,040
Whatever, just calm down.

260
00:14:52,040 --> 00:14:53,780
Cry on my shoulder, just like old times.

261
00:14:53,780 --> 00:14:54,900
We're best buds, right?

262
00:14:55,260 --> 00:14:57,290
Take off your clothes, Gray...

263
00:14:57,560 --> 00:14:59,980
You two sure are close!

264
00:14:59,980 --> 00:15:01,960
Always fawning all over each other...

265
00:15:01,960 --> 00:15:04,890
Well, you and Levy fight too much, Lucy!

266
00:15:04,890 --> 00:15:07,710
W-Why is Lisanna here?

267
00:15:08,080 --> 00:15:12,760
Mira-san's little sister... She 
was supposed to have died, right?

268
00:15:13,080 --> 00:15:16,320
Then it's not that everyone 
has turned opposite.

269
00:15:17,710 --> 00:15:21,060
See? Mira hasn't changed at all.

270
00:15:21,430 --> 00:15:23,330
But the clincher is that.

271
00:15:25,810 --> 00:15:29,160
Doesn't that girl look a bit like you, Wendy?

272
00:15:29,160 --> 00:15:30,550
You think?

273
00:15:30,550 --> 00:15:32,790
Seems pretty similar.

274
00:15:32,790 --> 00:15:33,740
Me?!

275
00:15:38,040 --> 00:15:41,560
Not opposite... Different.

276
00:15:41,780 --> 00:15:43,550
T-Then that means...

277
00:15:44,100 --> 00:15:45,000
Right.

278
00:15:45,650 --> 00:15:50,010
These people are not the 
ones we are looking for.

279
00:15:52,020 --> 00:15:52,970
They're different people.

280
00:15:54,810 --> 00:15:55,970
They're from Edolas.

281
00:15:57,770 --> 00:15:59,850
They were here originally!

282
00:16:02,710 --> 00:16:04,760
It's not so unbelievable.

283
00:16:05,100 --> 00:16:07,190
Like, parallel worlds.

284
00:16:08,360 --> 00:16:11,600
Edolas has its own culture and history.

285
00:16:11,600 --> 00:16:14,480
There's a possibility it 
has its own Fairy Tail!

286
00:16:14,480 --> 00:16:15,550
But that's...

287
00:16:15,550 --> 00:16:19,550
This is the Fairy Tail that 
was in Edolas to begin with?

288
00:16:19,840 --> 00:16:23,630
Then where are the versions that we know?

289
00:16:23,630 --> 00:16:25,420
What the hell are you blabbing about?

290
00:16:25,420 --> 00:16:27,250
How should I know?

291
00:16:27,250 --> 00:16:29,500
That's what we're trying to find out.

292
00:16:31,460 --> 00:16:34,620
It'll be trouble to stay 
here any longer. Let's go.

293
00:16:36,240 --> 00:16:38,220
Carla, where are you going?

294
00:16:39,130 --> 00:16:40,380
To the Royal City!

295
00:16:40,380 --> 00:16:44,270
There should be a clue about what 
happened to the guild in the Royal City!

296
00:16:46,780 --> 00:16:48,550
It's the Fairy Hunter!

297
00:16:48,550 --> 00:16:50,880
The Fairy Hunter is here!

298
00:16:53,180 --> 00:16:56,910
You over there, cat! Where do you think 
you're going? It's dangerous outside!

299
00:16:57,360 --> 00:16:58,650
Crap!

300
00:16:58,650 --> 00:17:00,580
This location's been found out already?

301
00:17:00,580 --> 00:17:03,620
The people from the Kingdom 
are after us again...

302
00:17:03,620 --> 00:17:05,480
This is terrible!

303
00:17:05,480 --> 00:17:06,490
Kingdom?

304
00:17:06,710 --> 00:17:09,960
The people who sent us to Earthland.

305
00:17:13,920 --> 00:17:18,430
We're the enemies of Fairy Tail?

306
00:17:18,810 --> 00:17:20,720
Reactor ready for ignition.

307
00:17:20,720 --> 00:17:22,130
Coordinates set.

308
00:17:22,590 --> 00:17:27,430
Error compensation complete 
in 5, 4, 3, 2, 1...

309
00:17:27,430 --> 00:17:28,670
Connected to the marker!

310
00:17:28,670 --> 00:17:30,940
Shock absorber charged with magic!

311
00:17:30,940 --> 00:17:34,020
How long until the transmission 
magic circle, Levy?

312
00:17:34,020 --> 00:17:36,360
I'm working on it right now! Suck it, Lucy!

313
00:17:36,360 --> 00:17:37,820
It's gonna be too late!

314
00:17:38,190 --> 00:17:40,120
The Fairy Hunter is coming!

315
00:17:40,120 --> 00:17:41,980
I know that, sheesh!

316
00:17:41,980 --> 00:17:43,830
Stop blabbing and hurry up!

317
00:17:45,140 --> 00:17:46,790
Fairy Hunter?

318
00:17:48,170 --> 00:17:51,440
40% output for transmission threshold...

319
00:17:51,440 --> 00:17:52,440
43%...

320
00:17:52,760 --> 00:17:54,270
46%...

321
00:17:54,270 --> 00:17:55,050
51%!

322
00:17:55,890 --> 00:17:56,900
What?

323
00:17:59,280 --> 00:18:01,480
Keep your head on straight, you loser.

324
00:18:01,480 --> 00:18:02,820
Hurry up, Levy!

325
00:18:02,820 --> 00:18:04,500
There's no time to waste!

326
00:18:04,500 --> 00:18:05,470
Shut up!

327
00:18:06,100 --> 00:18:07,680
Output at 61%...

328
00:18:07,680 --> 00:18:08,750
63%!

329
00:18:08,750 --> 00:18:10,310
Two minutes until transmission!

330
00:18:10,560 --> 00:18:12,520
The air... is shaking...

331
00:18:12,520 --> 00:18:14,220
She's coming!

332
00:18:17,060 --> 00:18:18,420
What's that?

333
00:18:20,410 --> 00:18:21,890
The Fairy Hunter!

334
00:18:21,890 --> 00:18:22,900
What's that?

335
00:18:23,610 --> 00:18:26,160
The Kingdom is after Fairy Tail?

336
00:18:26,390 --> 00:18:27,540
But why?

337
00:18:27,810 --> 00:18:29,680
Isn't that obvious?

338
00:18:31,520 --> 00:18:32,580
Me?

339
00:18:32,860 --> 00:18:36,380
By order of the King, all 
wizard guilds were abolished.

340
00:18:36,890 --> 00:18:39,290
Only one is left in the world...

341
00:18:39,800 --> 00:18:40,930
The one right here.

342
00:18:42,720 --> 00:18:44,940
You came with Natsu, even 
though you didn't know?

343
00:18:45,460 --> 00:18:49,310
In other words, we're an underground guild.

344
00:18:50,730 --> 00:18:53,300
Okay! We've passed the critical 
point for transmission!

345
00:18:53,590 --> 00:18:55,420
Shock absorber activated!

346
00:18:55,420 --> 00:18:57,900
Transmission magic circle, expand!

347
00:18:59,650 --> 00:19:01,810
What is it now?

348
00:19:01,810 --> 00:19:03,250
M-My body!

349
00:19:03,250 --> 00:19:05,020
We're floating!

350
00:19:05,020 --> 00:19:07,210
Everyone, grab onto something!

351
00:19:07,210 --> 00:19:09,570
I want to grab onto you, Juvia-chan!

352
00:19:09,570 --> 00:19:11,350
God<i>damn</i>, you're suffocating!

353
00:19:11,350 --> 00:19:12,810
Transmission, activate!

354
00:19:13,510 --> 00:19:15,830
Ah... Will we transfer safely, I wonder?

355
00:19:15,830 --> 00:19:17,400
Cana-san, I will protect you!

356
00:19:17,400 --> 00:19:18,520
No, I will!

357
00:19:18,520 --> 00:19:21,940
Nee-chan, Lisanna... Hold onto me tight!

358
00:19:21,940 --> 00:19:24,430
It's shaking... Shaking!

359
00:19:45,070 --> 00:19:46,410
Transmission, eh?

360
00:19:49,580 --> 00:19:51,680
Transmission magic, I see.

361
00:19:51,680 --> 00:19:55,480
Using that much magical power so foolishly...

362
00:19:55,480 --> 00:19:57,520
They really are quite the troublesome bunch.

363
00:19:57,520 --> 00:19:59,380
That damn underground guild...

364
00:19:59,380 --> 00:20:01,300
Sugar Boy, you're here?

365
00:20:03,180 --> 00:20:07,230
Those fairies sure are 
quick at running, yes...

366
00:20:07,230 --> 00:20:10,820
They flit from one place to another, 
like flies... Damn vermin...

367
00:20:11,640 --> 00:20:14,690
You were quite close, Fairy Hunter.

368
00:20:14,690 --> 00:20:18,440
However, they won't be able to 
transfer too many more times.

369
00:20:18,440 --> 00:20:20,530
It's only a matter of time 
until you catch your prey.

370
00:20:21,270 --> 00:20:25,360
On another subject, it seems the 
giant Anima plan was a success.

371
00:20:25,730 --> 00:20:30,370
So, all Magic Regiment Captains 
are to return to the Royal City.

372
00:20:30,370 --> 00:20:32,990
The Earthland Fairy Tail was destroyed?

373
00:20:32,990 --> 00:20:35,240
More accurately, absorbed.

374
00:20:35,240 --> 00:20:38,250
Our king sure does things in a big way.

375
00:20:39,230 --> 00:20:41,920
What happened to the wizards that 
were absorbed from Earthland?

376
00:20:42,870 --> 00:20:43,920
In the Royal City.

377
00:20:44,650 --> 00:20:47,250
They've become a giant lacrima.

378
00:20:47,250 --> 00:20:48,920
Lovely.

379
00:20:48,920 --> 00:20:52,610
Now Edolas doesn't need to worry 
about magic power for the time being.

380
00:21:05,770 --> 00:21:08,230
Okay, children! Moving's complete!

381
00:21:08,230 --> 00:21:09,430
We're saved...

382
00:21:09,430 --> 00:21:11,380
Looks like we were able 
to transfer in one piece.

383
00:21:11,380 --> 00:21:12,660
Is everyone safe?

384
00:21:15,320 --> 00:21:16,670
Move?

385
00:21:16,670 --> 00:21:19,110
They moved the entire guild?

386
00:21:19,110 --> 00:21:20,160
Wow...

387
00:21:20,670 --> 00:21:24,220
See, Juvia-chan? All my 
layers came in handy, right?

388
00:21:24,220 --> 00:21:26,110
I'll give you my thanks. For now.

389
00:21:26,110 --> 00:21:28,210
Too much, as always...

390
00:21:28,210 --> 00:21:30,170
Are you okay, Cana-san?

391
00:21:30,170 --> 00:21:31,680
Yes, somehow...

392
00:21:32,990 --> 00:21:35,050
Lisanna, are you injured?

393
00:21:35,050 --> 00:21:37,190
I'm fine, Elf-niichan.

394
00:21:37,190 --> 00:21:39,810
What the hell were you taking your time for?

395
00:21:39,810 --> 00:21:41,140
That was damn close!

396
00:21:41,140 --> 00:21:43,760
Shut up! Try it yourself sometime!

397
00:21:43,760 --> 00:21:45,820
Why does it shake so much, anyway?

398
00:21:45,820 --> 00:21:47,580
'Cause you're too fat, that's why!

399
00:21:47,580 --> 00:21:48,930
Oh, yeah?! Say that again!

400
00:21:48,930 --> 00:21:50,200
Why, you...

401
00:21:50,200 --> 00:21:52,580
Who was that person before...

402
00:21:52,580 --> 00:21:54,130
What's the matter, Natsu?

403
00:21:54,130 --> 00:21:56,110
Has it been so long you forgot?

404
00:21:56,110 --> 00:21:57,250
As if!

405
00:21:58,570 --> 00:22:02,130
She's one of the captains of the 
Kingdom's Magic Regiments...

406
00:22:03,380 --> 00:22:05,040
Erza Knightwalker.

407
00:22:06,300 --> 00:22:09,260
Also known as Erza the Fairy Hunter.

408
00:22:12,580 --> 00:22:13,570
What...?

409
00:22:15,380 --> 00:22:16,440
Erza is...

410
00:22:17,530 --> 00:22:18,390
...our enemy?

411
00:23:55,700 --> 00:23:58,680
The Lucy here is pretty scary.

412
00:23:58,680 --> 00:24:01,920
Really? I think the Lucy over 
there is plenty scary herself.

413
00:24:01,920 --> 00:24:03,330
You might have a point there!

414
00:24:03,330 --> 00:24:09,080
Now that I think about it, Lucy here is scary 
enough to give Lucy there a run for her money.

415
00:24:09,080 --> 00:24:11,250
Uh, I'm starting to get confused.

416
00:24:11,250 --> 00:24:13,990
If we're there, and they're 
here, then which is which?

417
00:24:14,430 --> 00:24:16,870
Next time: The Key of Hope!

418
00:24:16,870 --> 00:24:20,490
Let's make it simple and 
call them Lucy A and Lucy B!

419
00:24:20,490 --> 00:24:23,390
Then this one's Lucy A, and 
that one's Lucy B, right?

420
00:24:23,390 --> 00:24:24,520
Which one is which?

421
00:24:24,520 --> 00:24:26,810


